00, 900, 900, 900, 900, 900, 900, 900, 900, 900, 1000, 1000, 1000, 1000, 1000, 1000, 1000, 1000, 1000, 1000, 1000]", "output": "1000"}], "query": "You are an expert Python programmer. You will be given a question (problem specification) and will generate a correct Python program that matches the specification and passes all tests.\n\n### Question:\nGiven an integer array nums, return the most frequent even element.\nIf there is a tie, return the smallest one. If there is no such element, return -1.\n \nExample 1:\n\nInput: nums = [0,1,2,2,4,4,1]\nOutput: 2\nExplanation:\nThe even elements are 0, 2, and 4. Of these, 2 and 4 appear the most.\nWe return the smallest one, which is 2.\nExample 2:\n\nInput: nums = [4,4,4,9,2,4]\nOutput: 4\nExplanation: 4 is the even element appears the most.\n\nExample 3:\n\nInput: nums = [29,47,21,41,13,37,25,7]\nOutput: -1\nExplanation: There is no even element.\n\n \nConstraints:\n\n1 <= nums.length <= 2000\n0 <= nums[i] <= 105\n\n\n\n### Format: You will use the following starter code to write the solution to the problem and enclose your code within delimiters.\n```python\nclass Solution:\n    def mostFrequentEven(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom collections import Counter\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def mostFrequentEven(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n        # Filter out even numbers\n        even_nums = [num for num in nums if num % 2 == 0]\n        \n        # If there are no even numbers, return -1\n        if not even_nums:\n            return -1\n        \n        # Count the frequency of each even number\n        frequency = Counter(even_nums)\n        \n        # Find the most frequent even number, with a tie-breaker of the smallest number\n        most_frequent = min(frequency, key=lambda x: (-frequency[x], x))\n        \n        return most_frequent\n```\n\nThis solution filters out the even numbers from the input list, counts their frequencies, and then determines the most frequent even number. In case of a tie, it returns the smallest even number with the highest frequency. If there are no even numbers, it returns -1.", "estimated_date": 1662854400000}